All measurements were made from slide­mounted specimens using stage­calibrated ocular micrometers on an interference­phase contrast microscope (

Fan & Zhang 
2004

) and are given in micrometers. In the material examined, n/n indicates number of slides/number of specimens. Measurements x (y–z): x is the measurement of the specimens (mostly is 
holotype
) from which figure was drawn; y–z is the range of measurements.

subSubSection.paragraph:
MALE (
Fig. 21–25
). Similar to adult female except: genital opening situated between coxae IV; aedeagus present; with a pair of anal suckers; without adanal setae; tarsus IV having 2 suckers. Complement of setae on legs as in adult female except tarsi IV with 3 + 1 dorsoapical spine + 3–5 ventroapical spines.

